- `monopoly simulate --n-games 100 --players 4 --strategy BuyEverything --strategy Trader --seed 42` — runs simulation, prints per-player win rate/avg turns/avg cash table
- `monopoly markov --top 10` — computes Markov stationary distribution, shows top-N squares (Jail = 11.72%)
- `monopoly tournament --n-games 50 --seed 42` — round-robin tournament with Elo ranking

### Design decisions
- **`ColorTargeted` excluded from tournament**: `run_parallel_simulations` re-instantiates strategies via `REGISTRY[name]()` without args — but it's still usable in `simulate` via `_STRATEGY_KWARGS` with `target_colors=["orange"]` default
- **Invalid strategy**: caught before any game logic; prints user-friendly message with valid names list (no `KeyError` traceback)
- **All 943 tests pass** — zero regressions
